<paragraph blockId="35.[189,508,1910,1939]" box="[189,508,1910,1939]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,508,1910,1939]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Molecular identification</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[187,1399,1963,2025]" lastBlockId="36.[189,1399,265,618]" lastPageId="36" lastPageNumber="37" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
The present phylogenetic analysis based on COI and 16S rRNA genes shows that there is strong support for the monophyly of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Navas" authorityYear="1912" box="[399,476,1998,2024]" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Baliga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[399,476,1998,2024]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Baliga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clade for Japanese species by BI, ML, and NJ methods, which, however, did not comprise 
<taxonomicName authority="Hassan &amp; Zheng &amp; Liu, 2022" authorityName="Hassan &amp; Zheng &amp; Liu" authorityYear="2022" box="[302,536,265,291]" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Baliga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kashmirensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[302,536,265,291]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Baliga kashmirensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[543,633,266,292]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[704,805,265,291]" name="Pakistan" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
. Based on COI genes, 
<taxonomicName authority="Hassan &amp; Zheng &amp; Liu, 2022" authorityName="Hassan &amp; Zheng &amp; Liu" authorityYear="2022" box="[1069,1302,265,291]" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Baliga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kashmirensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1069,1302,265,291]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Baliga kashmirensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1309,1399,266,292]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
was assigned to be within a monophylum with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rambur" authorityYear="1842" box="[724,894,302,327]" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Myrmeleon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tenuipennis">
<emphasis box="[724,894,302,327]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">M. tenuipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Miller &amp; Stange, 1999" authorityName="Miller &amp; Stange" authorityYear="1999" box="[948,1394,301,327]" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Myrmeleon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="taiwanensis">
<emphasis box="[948,1122,302,327]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">M. taiwanensis</emphasis>
Miller &amp; Stange, 1999
</taxonomicName>
. However, the monophyly of 
<taxonomicName authority="Hassan &amp; Zheng &amp; Liu, 2022" authorityName="Hassan &amp; Zheng &amp; Liu" authorityYear="2022" box="[525,759,338,364]" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Baliga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kashmirensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[525,759,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Baliga kashmirensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[766,856,338,364]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rambur" authorityYear="1842" box="[924,1095,338,363]" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Myrmeleon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tenuipennis">
<emphasis box="[924,1095,338,363]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">M. tenuipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Olivier" authorityYear="1811" box="[1111,1247,338,364]" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Myrmeleon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hyalinus">
<emphasis box="[1111,1247,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">M. hyalinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gerstaecker" authorityYear="1885" box="[1263,1391,338,364]" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Myrmeleon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trivialis">
<emphasis box="[1263,1391,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">M. trivialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1767" box="[283,456,374,400]" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Myrmeleon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="formicarius">
<emphasis box="[283,456,374,400]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">M. formicarius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clade is recovered with relatively low nodal support values. For now, the present phylogenetic analysis is largely focused on species identification due to incomplete taxon sampling. The genetic divergence between 
<taxonomicName authority="Hassan &amp; Zheng &amp; Liu, 2022" authorityName="Hassan &amp; Zheng &amp; Liu" authorityYear="2022" box="[516,697,447,473]" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Baliga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kashmirensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[516,697,447,473]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">B. kashmirensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[704,794,447,473]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and the species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1767" box="[1015,1146,447,473]" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Myrmeleon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1015,1146,447,473]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Myrmeleon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was 
<geoCoordinate box="[1205,1270,447,473]" degrees="0.139" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" precision="55" value="0.139">0.139</geoCoordinate>
<geoCoordinate box="[1270,1349,447,473]" degrees="0.188" direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" precision="55" value="-0.188">–0.188</geoCoordinate>
and that between this new species and the other species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Navas" authorityYear="1912" box="[816,893,483,509]" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Baliga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[816,893,483,509]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Baliga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was 
<geoCoordinate box="[952,1018,483,510]" degrees="0.153" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" precision="55" value="0.153">0.153</geoCoordinate>
<geoCoordinate box="[1018,1100,483,510]" degrees="0.186" direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" precision="55" value="-0.186">–0.186</geoCoordinate>
. The greatest intraspecific divergence (0.049) was found respectively in 
<taxonomicName authority="Hayashi &amp; Matsumoto, 2020" authorityName="Hayashi &amp; Matsumoto" authorityYear="2020" box="[702,1203,519,546]" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Baliga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ryukyuensis">
<emphasis box="[702,869,519,545]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">B. ryukyuensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hayashi H. &amp; Matsumoto R. &amp; Sugawara H. &amp; Liu X. Y." box="[874,1203,519,546]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" pagination="235 - 251" refId="ref16573" refString="Hayashi H., Matsumoto R., Sugawara H. &amp; Liu X. Y. 2020. Two new species of Baliga (Neuroptera: Myrmeleontidae: Myrmeleontinae) with the molecular phylogeny of the tribe Myrmeleontini in Japan. Japanese Journal of Systematic Entomology 26 (2): 235 - 251." type="journal article" year="2020">Hayashi &amp; Matsumoto, 2020</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Olivier" authorityYear="1811" box="[1256,1389,519,545]" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Myrmeleon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hyalinus">
<emphasis box="[1256,1389,519,545]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">M. hyalinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The minimum and maximum interspecific genetic divergence between species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Navas" authorityYear="1912" box="[1133,1210,556,582]" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Baliga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1133,1210,556,582]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Baliga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1767" box="[1268,1399,556,582]" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Myrmeleon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1268,1399,556,582]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Myrmeleon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
ranged from 
<geoCoordinate box="[337,403,592,618]" degrees="0.074" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" precision="55" value="0.074">0.074</geoCoordinate>
<geoCoordinate box="[403,484,592,618]" degrees="0.186" direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" precision="55" value="-0.186">–0.186</geoCoordinate>
, and 
<geoCoordinate box="[543,608,592,618]" degrees="0.123" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" precision="55" value="0.123">0.123</geoCoordinate>
<geoCoordinate box="[608,690,592,618]" degrees="0.188" direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" precision="55" value="-0.188">–0.188</geoCoordinate>
, respectively.
</paragraph>
